# SCOPE RULES - FLOW CDMX EVENT SITE
# Repo: cdmx.flownation.world
# Org: flowbondhq
# Purpose: Event site for FLOW CDMX (April 30, 2026)
# Stack: Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind, Supabase, Vercel

## HARD BOUNDARIES - NEVER VIOLATE

You operate EXCLUSIVELY inside this repository.

1. NEVER cd into any folder outside /Users/stephferrera/Projects/flowcdmx
2. NEVER reference, read, or modify files in:
   - /Users/stephferrera/Projects/flowbond/
   - /Users/stephferrera/Projects/flowbond-os/
   - /Users/stephferrera/Projects/flowbond-app/
   - /Users/stephferrera/Projects/FlowBond/
   - Any path outside this repo
3. NEVER clone, pull, or push to any other repository
4. If a task mentions another project, STOP and ask before acting
5. If you need context from another repo, ASK Steph to provide it manually

## GIT RULES - STRICT

1. NEVER commit or push directly to main
2. ALWAYS verify current branch before staging: git branch --show-current
3. ALWAYS work on feature branches: feat/, fix/, chore/, docs/
4. Commit messages: Conventional Commits format
5. Stage files explicitly with git add <file> - NEVER git add . or git add -A
6. Before any push, show Steph: branch, staged files, commit message
7. Never use: reset --hard, push --force, or destructive operations without approval

## BRAND — FLOW (never translate)

- Logo / hero display: **FLOW** (all caps).
- Formal event name: **FLOW CDMX** (all caps).
- Body copy: **Flow** (capitalized proper noun), never lowercase “flow” in sentences.
- Never use “flujo” as a stand-in for the brand name.

## REPO IDENTITY

This repo does ONE thing: the public website for the April 30 FLOW CDMX event.
It is NOT the FlowBond OS monorepo.
It is NOT the FlowBond core platform.
It will eventually be extracted to flowbond-os - but NOT NOW.

## WORKING STYLE

- Ask clarifying questions before destructive operations
- Show diffs before applying changes to more than 3 files
- When Steph says STOP, halt immediately and report state
- Never auto-approve terminal commands containing: rm, reset --hard, push --force
